# Views as Composers

Per DESIGN.md: **Views are the only layer that connects stores and IPC to the component tree.**

## Rules

- **`src/views/`** — May use `useXStore()`, `window.api`, Vue Router, and compose dumb components. This is the composition layer.
- **`src/components/`** — Must NOT import from stores or call IPC. Components are dumb: props in, events out.
- **`src/composables/`** — May use stores only if the composable is explicitly a "view hook" (e.g. `useOnboardingFlow` called by a view). Do not expose `window.api` or stores to composables intended for reuse by components.

## Examples

```vue
<!-- ✅ GOOD — view wires store and components -->
<script setup lang="ts">
import { useMealPlanStore } from '@/stores/meal-plan.store'
import MealCard from '@/components/meal/MealCard.vue'

const store = useMealPlanStore()
const plans = computed(() => store.plans)
</script>
```

```vue
<!-- ❌ BAD — component uses store -->
<script setup lang="ts">
import { useMealPlanStore } from '@/stores/meal-plan.store'
const store = useMealPlanStore() // belongs in a view
</script>
```
